1) To Get version of Docker  ->    docker --version

2) To Run image  -> docker run hello-world

3) To list out all the available images in the systems   -> docker images

4) To pull images from the docker hub to local repository -> docker pull [image name]

5) To Run image which create container from that image -> docker run -it -d [image name] 

6) To list out all the containers  -> docker ps -a

7) To logged in to the docker  -> docker login

8) To perform commands in containers -> docker exec -it [container ID] bash

9) To perform start and stop opration on container  -> docker start/stop [container ID]

10) To delete container -> docker rm -f [container ID]

11) To get more info -> docker info

12) 

